x4codes.hlp: Grand Accelerateur National d`Ions Lourds, Caen, France

x4freetext: The target area densities were of about 200 mg/cm**2.
two telescopes have been used. A first
one was placed in the reaction chamber at 9 degree
with respect to the beam direction. This telescope was
used to cross check the results of this experiment with
the 9 degree values of the previous one. The second
telescope was placed in the beam axis, at a distance of
768(5) mm behind the targets. The two telescopes were
made of a stack of two silicon detectors followed by a
CsI(Tl) crystal scintillator. The detector properties
thin Si thickness 146 mum, diameter 1.954 cm
thick Si thickness 1 mm, diameter 1.954 cm
A precise analysis of the beam monitor revealed a
nonlinearity of the plastic scintillator when five or
more incident ions per beam bunch are detected. By
taking into account this information, the beam monitor
calibration of the first experiment was corrected. As a
result, the data previously published in Dudouet et al.
(see REL-EF) have been corrected by about 5%.
